issue.title: Feature: Order History
issue.body:
Fetch the wallets smart contract history and display to the user. Allowing a transparent view of all orders/transactions made with Cirrus Swap.

**NOTE:** We likely want to group calls made for a particular order. 

In Example: Creating a sell order requires multiple contract calls.
1. Creating the sell order contract.
2. Approving the contract to handle the SRC amount to be sold
3. Adding the order to the orders contract

These three calls would be grouped together in the UI creating a clear and transparent view of exactly which calls were made for each action.

Discussion: Should Stratis Swap support _all_ contract calls? Even those outside of Stratis Swap?
Future implementations will allow for CSV exports for tax purposes so making this a one stop shop for that would require _all_ contract calls to be displayed.

Possibility: Only show Stratis Swap related calls in the UI but allow for csv export of **all** calls regardless of purpose.
